The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | IOC focus on fuel quality
                                                                                                               IOC focus on fuel quality
                            
	New Delhi, Feb. 11 (pti): Indian Oil Corporation will invest Rs 9,000 crore to improve the quality of petrol and diesel produced at its refineries, a company press release said.        
	According to the auto fuel policy, petrol and diesel quality for 13 major cities will be on a par with Euro-1V norms from April 1, 2010, and rest of the country will switch over to Euro-III quality.        
	IOC has installed a hydrocracker at its Haldia refinery and a diesel hydro-treater under the residue upgradation project at the Gujarat refinery to improve the diesel quality.        
	Additional reactors are also being installed at the diesel hydro-treatment unit at its Panipat and Barauni facilities to improve the diesel quality. The projects are expected to be commissioned by December, 2009, IOC director (refineries) B. N. Bankapur said.                                                                                                                                        
